title: Man Utd news: Roy Keane involves Chelsea in latest Jose Mourinho dig | Metro News
text:
Chris Davie for Metro.co.uk Tuesday 28 Feb 2017 2:56 am Roy Keane has not been impressed with Jose Mourinho’s changes at United. (NurPhoto/Getty Images) 
Roy Keane admits he has not been impressed with Jose Mourinho’s reign at Manchester United and believes their true test will come when they next face Chelsea. 
United are currently sixth in the table having not lost a Premier League game since the 4-0 defeat to Antonio Conte’s side on October 23. 
Mourinho’s men are on a run of six consecutive victories in all competitions but Keane has questioned the amount of progress the team has shown this season. 
‘I’ve very little time for Mourinho. I look at United and the run they’re on now,’ Keane said at a fundraiser event before United’s 3-2 victory over Southampton in the EFL Cup final. United beat Southampton in the EFL Cup final on Sunday. (Getty Images) 
‘They’re sixth in the league. People are like, ‘I can see progress’– [but] they’re sixth in the league. 
‘They’ve beaten no one in three months.
